<subSubSection lastPageId="14" lastPageNumber="49" pageId="13" pageNumber="48" type="key">
<keyStep pageId="13" pageNumber="48">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1436,1557,2018]" box="[151,1435,1557,1578]" pageId="13" pageNumber="48">
<keyLead box="[151,1435,1557,1578]" pageId="13" pageNumber="48">
<number box="[151,163,1557,1578]" pageId="13" pageNumber="48" value="1.0">1</number>
Katepisternum with large shining spot. Antenna with postpedicel about 
<number box="[913,943,1557,1578]" pageId="13" pageNumber="48" value="2.5">2.5</number>
times as long as wide..... 
<taxonomicName authority="Melander" authorityName="Melander" box="[1222,1435,1557,1578]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Platypalpus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arnaudi">
<emphasis box="[1222,1322,1557,1578]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="48">P. arnaudi</emphasis>
(Melander)
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1436,1557,2018]" box="[151,1436,1586,1607]" pageId="13" pageNumber="48">
<keyLead box="[151,1436,1586,1607]" pageId="13" pageNumber="48">
– Katepisternum entirely tomentose. Antenna with short postpedicel which is at most 
<number box="[1029,1059,1586,1607]" pageId="13" pageNumber="48" value="1.5">1.5</number>
times as long as wide........... 
<number box="[1424,1436,1586,1607]" pageId="13" pageNumber="48" value="2.0">2</number>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="13" pageNumber="48">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1436,1557,2018]" box="[151,1436,1615,1636]" pageId="13" pageNumber="48">
<keyLead box="[151,1436,1615,1636]" pageId="13" pageNumber="48">
<number box="[151,163,1615,1636]" pageId="13" pageNumber="48" value="2.0">2</number>
Dorsocentral bristles uniserial. Male: mid tibia with short, black, claw-like apical spur................ 
<taxonomicName authority="Melander" authorityName="Melander" box="[1258,1436,1615,1636]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Platypalpus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="canus">
<emphasis box="[1258,1338,1615,1636]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="48">P. canus</emphasis>
Melander
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1436,1557,2018]" box="[151,1436,1645,1666]" pageId="13" pageNumber="48">
<keyLead box="[151,1436,1645,1666]" pageId="13" pageNumber="48">
– Dorsocentral bristles at least anteriorly arranged in 
<number box="[704,738,1645,1666]" pageId="13" pageNumber="48" value="2.5" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.0">2–3</number>
(or more) irregular rows. Mid tibia without apical spur in both sexes... 
<number box="[1424,1436,1645,1666]" pageId="13" pageNumber="48" value="3.0">3</number>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="13" pageNumber="48">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1436,1557,2018]" box="[151,1435,1674,1695]" pageId="13" pageNumber="48">
<keyLead box="[151,1435,1674,1695]" pageId="13" pageNumber="48">
<number box="[151,163,1674,1695]" pageId="13" pageNumber="48" value="3.0">3</number>
Legs brown, only knees of fore pair somewhat paler........................................ 
<taxonomicName authority="Melander" authorityName="Melander" box="[1233,1435,1674,1695]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Platypalpus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="syletor">
<emphasis box="[1233,1322,1674,1695]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="48">P. syletor</emphasis>
(Melander)
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1436,1557,2018]" box="[151,1436,1703,1724]" pageId="13" pageNumber="48">
<keyLead box="[151,1436,1703,1724]" pageId="13" pageNumber="48">
– Legs yellow, at most some tarsomeres brownish............................................................. 
<number box="[1424,1436,1703,1724]" pageId="13" pageNumber="48" value="4.0">4</number>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="13" pageNumber="48">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1436,1557,2018]" pageId="13" pageNumber="48">
<keyLead pageId="13" pageNumber="48">
<number box="[151,163,1733,1754]" pageId="13" pageNumber="48" value="4.0">4</number>
Antenna with scape and pedicel yellow, postpedicel brown. Palpus yellow. Male: right epandrial lamella cleft apically (
<figureCitation box="[1355,1423,1733,1754]" captionStart="FIGURES 18 – 20" captionStartId="10.[151,263,808,831]" captionTargetBox="[155,1429,197,778]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,193,787]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 18 – 20. Platypalpus submicrophona sp. nov., male. 18. right epandrial lamella, lateral view. 19. cerci and epandrium, dorsal view. 20. left epandrial lamella and left cercus, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/282724/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="48">
Fig. 
<number box="[1399,1423,1733,1754]" pageId="13" pageNumber="48" value="18.0">18</number>
</figureCitation>
)................................................................................ 
<taxonomicName box="[1177,1352,1762,1783]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Platypalpus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="submicrophona" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1177,1352,1762,1783]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="48">P. submicrophona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1359,1435,1762,1783]" pageId="13" pageNumber="48" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1359,1435,1762,1783]" pageId="13" pageNumber="48">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1436,1557,2018]" box="[151,1436,1791,1812]" pageId="13" pageNumber="48">
<keyLead box="[151,1436,1791,1812]" pageId="13" pageNumber="48">
– Antenna brown. Palpus brown (except 
<taxonomicName box="[599,737,1791,1812]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Platypalpus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="microphona">
<emphasis box="[599,737,1791,1812]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="48">P. microphona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Male: right epandrial lamella more or less rounded apically....... 
<number box="[1424,1436,1791,1812]" pageId="13" pageNumber="48" value="5.0">5</number>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="13" pageNumber="48">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1436,1557,2018]" pageId="13" pageNumber="48">
<keyLead pageId="13" pageNumber="48">
<number box="[151,163,1821,1842]" pageId="13" pageNumber="48" value="5.0">5</number>
Scutum almost uniformly covered with very short setulae, acrostichals and dorsocentrals undifferentiated. Halter with pale yel- low stem and darkened knob. Male: left epandrial lamella pointed apically, with scattered, moderately long, marginal setae ventrally (
<figureCitation box="[323,393,1879,1900]" captionStart="FIGURES 21 – 23" captionStartId="11.[151,263,1621,1644]" captionTargetBox="[165,1388,989,1596]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,983,1599]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 21 – 23. Platypalpus tanbarkiensis sp. nov., male. 21. right epandrial lamella, lateral view. 22. cerci and epandrium, dorsal view. 23. left epandrial lamella and left cercus, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/282725/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="48">
Fig. 
<number box="[368,393,1879,1900]" pageId="13" pageNumber="48" value="23.0">23</number>
</figureCitation>
).................................................................. 
<taxonomicName box="[1194,1347,1879,1900]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Platypalpus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tanbarkiensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1194,1347,1879,1900]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="48">P. tanbarkiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1353,1429,1879,1900]" pageId="13" pageNumber="48" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1353,1429,1879,1900]" pageId="13" pageNumber="48">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1436,1557,2018]" pageId="13" pageNumber="48">
<keyLead pageId="13" pageNumber="48">
– Acrostichals separated from dorsocentrals by bare space. Halter uniformly pale yellow. Male: left epandrial lamella rounded apically, with numerous very long setae sitting fan-like on ventral tubercle (unknown in 
<taxonomicName box="[1071,1210,1938,1959]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Platypalpus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="microphona">
<emphasis box="[1071,1210,1938,1959]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="48">P. microphona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
)................ 
<number box="[1424,1436,1938,1959]" pageId="13" pageNumber="48" value="6.0">6</number>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="13" pageNumber="48">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1436,1557,2018]" box="[151,1435,1967,1988]" pageId="13" pageNumber="48">
<keyLead box="[151,1435,1967,1988]" pageId="13" pageNumber="48">
<number box="[151,163,1967,1988]" pageId="13" pageNumber="48" value="6.0">6</number>
Palpus yellow. Male unknown....................................................... 
<taxonomicName authority="Melander" authorityName="Melander" box="[1183,1435,1967,1988]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Platypalpus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="microphona">
<emphasis box="[1183,1322,1967,1988]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="48">P. microphona</emphasis>
(Melander)
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1436,1557,2018]" box="[151,1436,1997,2018]" pageId="13" pageNumber="48">
<keyLead box="[151,1436,1997,2018]" pageId="13" pageNumber="48">
– Palpus brown........................................................................................ 
<number box="[1424,1436,1997,2018]" pageId="13" pageNumber="48" value="7.0">7</number>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="14" pageNumber="49">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1436,151,261]" pageId="14" pageNumber="49">
<keyLead pageId="14" pageNumber="49">
<number box="[151,163,151,172]" pageId="14" pageNumber="49" value="7.0">7</number>
Dorsocentrals arranged in 
<number box="[481,517,151,172]" pageId="14" pageNumber="49" value="2.5" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.0">2–3</number>
irregular rows. Fore tarsus yellow. Male: left epandrial lamella with finger-like projection apically (
<figureCitation box="[285,353,181,202]" captionStart="FIGURES 15 – 17" captionStartId="8.[151,263,1683,1706]" captionTargetBox="[176,1423,1073,1657]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[153,1438,1061,1662]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 15 – 17. Platypalpus layiaphilus sp. nov., male. 15. right epandrial lamella, lateral view. 16. cerci and epandrium, dorsal view. 17. left epandrial lamella and left cercus, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/282723/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="49">
Fig. 
<number box="[329,353,181,202]" pageId="14" pageNumber="49" value="17.0">17</number>
</figureCitation>
)....................................................................... 
<taxonomicName box="[1223,1353,181,202]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Platypalpus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="layiaphilus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1223,1353,181,202]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="49">P. layiaphilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1359,1435,181,202]" pageId="14" pageNumber="49" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1359,1435,181,202]" pageId="14" pageNumber="49">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1436,151,261]" pageId="14" pageNumber="49">
<keyLead pageId="14" pageNumber="49">
– Dorsocentrals more numerous, not arranged in regular rows and undifferentiated from supra-alar setulae. Fore tarsomeres 
<number box="[1400,1436,210,231]" pageId="14" pageNumber="49" value="3.5" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="2.0">2–5</number>
yellowish brown. Male: left epandrial lamella broadly rounded apically (
<figureCitation box="[922,991,239,260]" captionStart="FIGURES 12 – 14" captionStartId="7.[151,263,1974,1997]" captionTargetBox="[151,1417,1416,1934]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,1378,1953]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 12 – 14. Platypalpus cummingi sp. nov., male. 12. right epandrial lamella, lateral view. 13. cerci and epandrium, dorsal view. 14. left epandrial lamella and left cercus, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/282722/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="49">
Fig. 
<number box="[966,991,239,260]" pageId="14" pageNumber="49" value="14.0">14</number>
</figureCitation>
).................. 
<taxonomicName box="[1229,1347,240,261]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Platypalpus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cummingi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1229,1347,240,261]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="49">P. cummingi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1353,1429,239,260]" pageId="14" pageNumber="49" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1353,1429,239,260]" pageId="14" pageNumber="49">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
